1. Software Sovereignty
Foma is a 'buy-to-own' product. The Company grants you a personal, non-exclusive, non-transferable, perpetual license to install and use the Software solely for your creative writing purposes. The Company treats this like a physical purchase: once you buy it, it is yours to use on your hardware indefinitely. The Company cannot 'switch off' your software or lock you out of your files. You may not sublicense, rent, or distribute the Software.

Users who purchase Foma at a 'Founders' or discounted introductory rate enjoy the same perpetual license and sovereignty as full-price purchasers. Your early support is recognized as a completed 'honest trade' for the version of Foma that you have acquired.

2. Intellectual Property
The Software, including all code, design, and assets, is and remains the exclusive property of the Company. You own the Copy (the instance of Foma on your machine) and the Content (everything you write). Your own creative work produced using the Software remains entirely your property.

3. Restrictions
