4. Data & Privacy
All project files are stored locally on your device. The Software does not collect, transmit, or share your creative content. Optional GitHub sync is performed at your explicit direction and governed by GitHub's own terms of service. Foma operates local-first. It does not 'phone home'. No telemetry, usage tracking, or automated crash reporting is active. If the software crashes, a log may be generated locally on your device; this log is never transmitted to the Company unless you manually and explicitly choose to email it to us for support.

5. Updates
You are never forced to update Foma. While the Company may issue updates to improve features or security, you may continue using your current version under the terms you originally agreed to indefinitely. If you choose to install a major update that includes a revised Agreement, you will be prompted to review and accept the new terms before using the updated software. The Company may issue updates that modify features or this Agreement. However, changes to the software or to this Agreement will only apply to the updated version of the Software.

